description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a highly motivated Medical Examiner Officer to join the Quality and Risk Team as we extend the programme to community deaths. This post is a key post in supporting the Trusts mortality process, and will provide support to a range of staff within the Trust and be a point of contact and source of advice for relatives of deceased patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The purpose of this role is to be the in-house expert for the mortality process with the aim of improving reporting and trend analysis and therefore the quality and effectiveness of clinical services and patient care. You will support the medical examiner in their role in scrutinising the circumstances and causes of death and assist in ensuring staff are fully trained and supported so that the Trust is able to utilise the system to its fullest potential. You will require the ability to demonstrate empathy and remain professional at all times as there is likely to be a significant emotional effort associated with dealing with bereaved families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This part time post will be based at Poole Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note: if this job requires you to have a DBS check to enable you to properly fulfil the requirements of the job, on appointment you will be required to repay the cost of obtaining a DBS check and this amount will be reclaimed from your salary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 12/10/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Becky Protopsaltis (Medical Examiner Officer)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: becky.protopsaltis@rbch.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01202 704160&lt;/p&gt;
